sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260416T054258Z_1776346678.log:2937:+sdp/logs/Lead_T-004_20260408T223256Z_1775689515.log:1413:./sdp/logs/Lead_T-003_20260408T223256Z_1775689060.log:959:./sdp/logs/Lead_T-002_20260408T223256Z_1775688740.log:41:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-08T22:52:23.868Z","role":"user","content":"# Task T-002@20260408T223256Z: Add dual-socket model-per-role routing configuration mapping task categories to specific Ollama models and NUMA-pinned ports (11434 for socket 0, 11435 for socket 1).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Configuration maps coding, review, netops, orchestrator, and default roles to model names and ports<br/>- Model names are configurable without code changes (env var or config file)<br/>- Tests verify routing returns correct model+port for each category\n\n**Tier:** T1 — Light (Bug fix / config change / minor update)\n\n## Instructions\n\nRead the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\n\n**ADP Phases:** Implement → Verify → Commit\n\n1. Implement the fix or change described above.\n2. Ensure all existing tests pass.\n3. Add a regression test if the bug was not previously caught.\n4. Commit with a descriptive message: `fix(scope): short summary [T-002@20260408T223256Z]`\n\n## Rules\n\n- No spec required. Task description + commit message is sufficient.\n- Existing tests MUST pass after your change.\n- Follow existing code patterns and conventions.\n- Do not modify files outside the scope of this task.\n- Log any concerns to ESCALATIONS.md.\n\n## Validation\n\nRun before committing:\n```bash\npip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/\n```\n\nAll must pass.\n"}
sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260416T054258Z_1776346678.log:2938:+sdp/logs/Lead_T-004_20260408T223256Z_1775689515.log:1415:./sdp/logs/Lead_T-003_20260408T223256Z_1775689060.log:989:./my-claw/sdp/prd-gap-analyzer.md:50:| GA-007 | Create `gap_analyzer/e2e_runner.py` — per-PRD end-to-end integration tests. For each PRD, define a smoke test that exercises the full workflow: (1) Art Studio: call art_engine.generate_art() and verify output file exists in gallery/renders/. (2) Pet System: create a pet, feed it, check stats update. (3) Gallery: verify service running, art directory has files, framebuffer accessible. (4) Narrative Engine: instantiate engine, verify world state DB created. Tests use real local resources (Ollama, SQLite) but mock external APIs (Telegram, cloud agents). | T2 |
sdp/logs/Verify_T-001_20260416T054258Z_1776346678.log:2939:+sdp/logs/Lead_T-004_20260408T223256Z_1775689515.log:1416:./sdp/logs/Lead_T-003_20260408T223256Z_1775689060.log:990:./my-claw/sdp/prd-gap-analyzer.md:55:| GA-012 | Create E2E test suite in `tests/test_e2e_integration.py`. One test per PRD that's marked "complete" in the database. Each test exercises the full workflow for that PRD's feature set. Tests must pass in the gate alongside unit tests. Start with: test_glyphweave_dsl_renders, test_gallery_display_loads, test_pet_system_lifecycle, test_observatory_records. | T2 |
